# Electron Build Workflow

After making changes to the electron-vite-project, always:

1. **Kill old processes** — Stop any running WR Desk / Electron instances so the new build can replace files
2. **Rebuild** — Run `npm run build` from `apps/electron-vite-project`

## Commands

```powershell
# 1. Kill processes
taskkill /F /IM "WR Desk*" /T 2>$null; Get-Process | Where-Object { $_.ProcessName -like "*electron*" -or $_.ProcessName -like "*WR*" } | ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.Id -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue }

# 2. Rebuild
cd apps/electron-vite-project; npm run build
```

## Rationale

- Locked files prevent clean builds and deletions
- Fresh build ensures changes are testable immediately
